result.execSummary:
The defendant Brittany L Olson was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Fail/Report to County Jail (<10 Days), a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 946.425(1m)(a).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

supervisions.notes: To pay the costs of the action. 60 days to pay costs or set up payment plan with the Clerk of Courts office.
Huber release and good time granted. 60 days to report.

Defendant Brittany L Olson in court with attorney Gregory A. Gerbers.  Raymond L. Pelrine appeared for the State of Wisconsin.   Minute sheet. State moves to amend charge to Misdemeanor Failure to Report to Jail, gives plea agreement.  Court questions defendant on change of plea.  Rights/elements/max. penalties reviewed with defendant.  Defendant enters no contest plea to amended charge. Defense stipulates to factual basis to accept plea.  Court finds plea made freely, knowingly and voluntarily, accepts plea, and finds guilty of Misdemeanor Failure to Report to Jail. Bond is no longer in effect.
Defendant was fingerprinted 2/16/14 by jail staff. (fingerprint card destroyed 4/03/14)
To be fingerprinted and photographed before leaving the Justice Center.

Defendant Brittany L Olson in court with attorney Gregory A. Gerbers.  Defendant Brittany L Olson in custody.  Raymond L Pelrine appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Court reviews charge(s), max. penalties, right to counsel, right to preliminary hearing. Defense waives reading of the complaint, waives time limit for prelim.
